    "content": "nullReport and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Report and Reduce Your Carbon Footprint with Net Zero Cloud\n Get Ready to Use Net Zero Cloud\n Determine the Sources to Inventory\n Emissions Factors That Affect Calculations\n Create Your Consumption Records\n Manage Scope 3 Value Chain Data\n Manage Your Carbon Footprint\n Manage Your Water Footprint\n Manage the Annual Emissions Inventory\n Record Locking and Recalculation\n Benchmark Building Energy Intensity Data\n Manage Carbon Footprint Data Gaps\n Set Emissions Targets\n Emissions Forecasting\n Carbon Accounting for Extended Organizational Boundaries\n Carbon Accounting for Partner Community Users\n Engage Suppliers for Emissions Reduction\n Allocate Carbon Credits to Offset Unavoidable Emissions\n Allocate Energy Attribute Certificate Credits to Reduce Scope 2...\n Report Social and Governance Data with Net Zero Cloud\n Generate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n How to Generate Disclosures Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n Capture Reusable Data Using Document Clause Library\n Author Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms\n Author Disclosures by Using Microsoft 365 Word\n Author Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms and Microsoft 365 Word\n Design Document Templates in Microsoft 365 Word\n Einstein Generative AI For ESG Report Generation\n Create GRI Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create CDP Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create SASB Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Create ESRS Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\n Data Collection\n Improve Decarbonization Strategy with Sustainability Programs\n Data Auditing\n Submit Records for Approval\n Use Net Zero Analytics App\n Use DEI Analytics App\n Report Your Carbon Footprint\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nREPORT AND REDUCE YOUR CARBON FOOTPRINT WITH NET ZERO CLOUD\nGenerate Disclosures by Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\n\nBy using Disclosure and Compliance Hub, you can extract data, answer questions, and order responses logically. Net Zero Cloud guides you through a flow that simplifies and makes the creation of responses more efficient. Collaborate on the responses with other users, create a collection of reusable responses that are audited and approved. Then, you can use the responses to produce formatted documents.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nHow to Generate Disclosures Using Disclosure and Compliance Hub\nNet Zero Cloud managers use the Disclosure and Compliance Hub to generate disclosures by gathering qualitative and quantitative responses to questionnaires. You can create formatted disclosures by using a guided process to extract data from Salesforce objects and other data sources.\nCapture Reusable Data Using Document Clause Library\nStore the reusable data from reporting standards’ templates that have questions that are similar in a document clause library. You can use the clause library to draft, get approvals for, and store these frequently used and pre-canned responses. Additionally, use interest tags within the clause library to organize responses.\nAuthor Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms\nAuthor disclosure reports and add clauses by using OmniScript forms and Discovery Framework.\nAuthor Disclosures by Using Microsoft 365 Word\nAuthor disclosure reports directly in Microsoft 365 Word by using the Salesforce Disclosure and Compliance Hub for Microsoft 365 Word add-in. You can access data in Salesforce while authoring a disclosure.\nAuthor Disclosures by Using OmniScript Forms and Microsoft 365 Word\nAuthor disclosure reports that use OmniScript and Microsoft 365 Word by using the Salesforce Disclosure and Compliance Hub for Microsoft 365 Word add-in. You can access the data in Salesforce when you author a disclosure.\nDesign Document Templates in Microsoft 365 Word\nQuickly and efficiently maintain document templates by using the Disclosure and Compliance Hub for Microsoft 365 Word add-in. Use the template designer to generate documents with a structure that the Disclosure and Compliance Hub can comprehend and offer an intelligent authoring experience to end users. Create and edit template documents, and simplify the search for elements, such as questions within the templates. The embedded Word features help prevent syntax errors, and provide a smooth editing and saving experience.\nEinstein Generative AI For ESG Report Generation\nMost companies are expected to file different types of environment, social, and governance (ESG) reports periodically to disclose carbon emissions that they own for their operations. Reports include the company initiatives for reducing carbon emissions. Most of the information in these reports remains consistent, so you can often reuse it between different report types. However, the content is scattered throughout multiple documents, or multiple frameworks.\nCreate GRI Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\nCreate disclosures that your company shares with external shareholders by using the disclosures template for GRI standards implemented on Disclosure and Compliance Hub. You can include the disclosures report in your GRI Standards report.\nCreate CDP Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\nCreate disclosures that your company shares with external shareholders by using the disclosures template for CDP implemented on Disclosure and Compliance Hub. You can include the disclosures report in your CDP report.\nCreate SASB Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\nCreate disclosures that your company shares with external shareholders by using the disclosures template for SASB implemented on Disclosure and Compliance Hub. You can include the disclosures report in your SASB report.\nCreate ESRS Disclosures Report by Using the Net Zero Cloud Template\nCreate disclosures that your company shares with external shareholders by using the disclosures template for European Sustainability Reporting Standards (ESRS) implemented on Disclosure and Compliance Hub.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
